<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q59_v9" title="Q59_v9" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Un estanque metálico de base rectangular tiene dimensiones interiores de 4,2 m de largo y 3,1 m de ancho. En el fondo se instaló una capa aislante horizontal de 0,1 m de espesor, de modo que la altura disponible para el agua se reduce en esa cantidad respecto de la altura interior total del estanque, que es de 2,0 m. El estanque está lleno hasta el borde.</p>
    <p>Se desea conocer la cantidad de agua contenida para aplicar correctamente un producto limpiador. 
    
    
    ¿Cuál es el volumen de agua contenido en el estanque, en metros cúbicos (
      <m:math>
        <m:msup>
          <m:mi>m</m:mi>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn>
        </m:msup>
      </m:math>
    )?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">26,04m^(3)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La altura disponible para el agua no es <m:math><m:mn>2,0</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:math>, porque la capa aislante ocupa <m:math><m:mn>0,1</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:math>. Entonces, la altura del agua es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,0</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>0,1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. El volumen correcto es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4,2</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>3,1</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>13,02</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24,738</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, que no es <m:math><m:mn>26,04</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">24,738m^(3)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La altura disponible para el agua es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,0</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>0,1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> m. Entonces, el volumen es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4,2</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>3,1</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>13,02</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24,738</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <m:math><m:msup><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msup></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">23,436m^(3)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La altura del agua debe ser <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,0</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>0,1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> m. Con esa altura, el volumen es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4,2</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>3,1</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24,738</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Por lo tanto, <m:math><m:mn>23,436</m:mn></m:math> no corresponde al volumen pedido.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">25,42m^(3)<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Primero se calcula la altura disponible para el agua: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,0</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>0,1</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> m. Luego, el volumen es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4,2</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>3,1</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>1,9</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24,738</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <m:math><m:msup><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msup></m:math>. Ese resultado es distinto de <m:math><m:mn>25,42</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso del volumen del estanque</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar las dimensiones de la base</strong></p>
            <p>El estanque tiene base rectangular de largo <m:math><m:mn>4,2</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:math> y ancho <m:math><m:mn>3,1</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular la altura disponible para el agua</strong></p>
            <p>La altura interior total es <m:math><m:mn>2,0</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:math>, pero hay una capa aislante horizontal de espesor <m:math><m:mn>0,1</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:math> en el fondo.</p>
            <p>Entonces, la altura disponible para el agua es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2,0</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>0,1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1,9</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              m
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Calcular el área de la base</strong></p>
            <p>El área de la base rectangular es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>4,2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3,1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>13,02</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, el área de la base es <m:math><m:mn>13,02</m:mn></m:math> <m:math><m:msup><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Calcular el volumen de agua</strong></p>
            <p>El volumen de un prisma rectangular se calcula multiplicando área de la base por altura:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>13,02</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1,9</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>24,738</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces, el volumen de agua contenido en el estanque es <m:math><m:mn>24,738</m:mn></m:math> <m:math><m:msup><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msup></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>B</strong>: <m:math><m:mn>24,738</m:mn></m:math> <m:math><m:msup><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msup></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>